{"lemma":"حِصانٌ","slug":"حِصانٌ","root":"ح.ص.ن","root_slug":"ح-ص-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ص-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8273","n8274"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%90%D8%B5%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"horse"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"stallion, stud, sire"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"knight"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"horsepower"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ħi.sˤaːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8273","headword_ar":"حَصَانٌ","root":"HSn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaASinN","text_ar":"حَاصِنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaASinapN","text_ar":"حَاصِنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSonaA='u","text_ar":"حَصْنَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHoSinapN","text_ar":"مُحْصِنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, S, Mgh, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHoSanapN","text_ar":"مُحْصَنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th, S, Msb, K,) applied to a woman,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Continent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chaste;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abstaining from what is not lawful nor decorous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, S, Mgh, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from that which induces suspicion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil opinion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh and TA in explanation of the first of these epithets:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"married; having a husband:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSaAnN","text_ar":"حَصَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has both of these significations: (Ham p. 101:) and accord. to Th, (S,) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHoSanapN","text_ar":"مُحْصَنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h only, has the latter signification; (S, Mgh, * Msb; *) and means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused to be continent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chaste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to abstain from that which is unlawful"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"indecorous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by her husband: (Mgh: [and the same is implied in the S:]) and this epithet is also applied to a woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emancipated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having become a Muslimeh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA:) [certain particular applications of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHoSinapN","text_ar":"مُحْصِنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"have been implicatively shown above: see 4:] the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSaAnN","text_ar":"حَصَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuSunN","text_ar":"حُصُنٌ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":587},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSaAnaAtN","text_ar":"حَصَانَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaASinN","text_ar":"حَاصِنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaASinapN","text_ar":"حَاصِنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaASinu","text_ar":"حَوَاصِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaASanaAtN","text_ar":"حَاصَنَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the former of which ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HwASn","text_ar":"حواصن"},{"kind":"text","text":") also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pregnant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) applied to women: (TA:) the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mHSnAt","text_ar":"محصنات"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the first instance of its occurrence in ch. iv. [verse 28] of the Kur, is read by all ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHoSanaAt","text_ar":"مُحْصَنَات","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A 'Obeyd, TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having husbands;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, Mgh, Msb, TA;) because when such women are made captives, their marriage-tie is cut: but in other instances, some read thus, understanding it in the sense last explained; and others read ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHoSinaAt","text_ar":"مُحْصِنَات","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that have become Muslimehs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, TA:) in the Kur iv. 29, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free"},{"kind":"text","text":"women: and in the Kur v. 7,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chaste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"women: (Mgh: [in the Msb, it is said to have the latter of these last two meaning in iv. 29, and the former of them in v. 7:]) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHoSanaAt","text_ar":"مُحْصَنَات","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the more common in the language of the Arabs. (Fr, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSaAnN","text_ar":"حَصَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A pearl,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large pearl;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dur~apN","text_ar":"دُرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) because it is protected in the interior of the shell that contains it. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","Th","Az","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n8274","headword_ar":"حِصَانٌ","root":"HSn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high-bred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"horse, (Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of whose seed one is niggardly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"horse: (Mgh, K:) or this latter is a secondary meaning, originating from frequency of usage: (S, Msb:) or a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stallion"},{"kind":"text","text":"horse; or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fit to cover:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAHa","text_ar":"رَاحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiSaAn","text_ar":"حِصَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is. so called because he preserves his rider: (TA:) or because his back is like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiSon","text_ar":"حِصْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"to his rider; (Mgh, Msb;) wherefore horses are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuSuwnN","text_ar":"حُصُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) or because one is niggardly of his seed, so that he is not made to cover any but a generous mare: (S, Mgh, Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuSunN","text_ar":"حُصُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh, Msb, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","Mgh","S","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}